_

04:27.808 --> 04:30.193
[Groans]

05:04.461 --> 05:07.681
[Coughs]

05:08.418 --> 05:12.598
_

05:16.857 --> 05:18.808
Yes, hello, this is David Linn

05:18.826 --> 05:20.410
from <i>The New York Times.</i>

05:20.444 --> 05:22.145
May I speak with Susan, please?

05:22.163 --> 05:23.813
Thank you.

05:23.831 --> 05:26.116
[Wind howls]

05:27.418 --> 05:29.786
Hi, Susan, it's David again.

05:29.820 --> 05:33.206
I was just calling
to see if we can set--

05:33.257 --> 05:34.874
Well, yes, well, I figured

05:34.925 --> 05:37.493
we have to do
the interview by phone

05:37.511 --> 05:39.662
since they've already
left New York.

05:39.680 --> 05:41.264
But what we'd
really love to get

05:41.298 --> 05:43.183
is a photo of
Mr. and Mrs. Schwartz

05:43.217 --> 05:45.552
to go along with the article.

05:45.603 --> 05:48.805
When-- when are they
scheduled to get home?

05:50.941 --> 05:54.110
Oh, so they'll be home tonight.

05:54.145 --> 05:55.845
Gotcha.

05:55.863 --> 05:57.447
Now, the address I have on them

05:57.481 --> 05:59.399
is Upper Canyon Road.

05:59.450 --> 06:01.067
Is that still...

06:01.118 --> 06:02.986
No, it isn't.
They've-- Oh.

06:03.020 --> 06:05.205
Let me get a pen.

06:05.239 --> 06:07.040
Where do they...

06:07.074 --> 06:10.493
Tesuque, I see.

06:10.527 --> 06:12.295
And the address?

06:14.632 --> 06:16.499
Is that-- is that
up near the opera house?

06:16.533 --> 06:19.869
I hear that's nice.

06:19.887 --> 06:22.255
Well, I'll be in contact
with my photographer

06:22.306 --> 06:24.707
to check on his schedule.

06:24.725 --> 06:26.643
No, no, it's--
it's their call.

06:26.677 --> 06:30.563
I know how busy
Mr. and Mrs. Schwartz are.

06:30.598 --> 06:31.931
Thank you.

06:31.982 --> 06:35.568
This should make
one hell of a story.

06:35.603 --> 06:37.604
Goodbye.

06:52.736 --> 06:54.120
[Elliott] I'm just saying

06:54.171 --> 06:56.572
it's apples and oranges.

06:56.590 --> 06:59.259
Listen, I maintain,

06:59.293 --> 07:01.795
if-- if--
if I want pizza,

07:01.846 --> 07:04.013
- I go to a pizza place.
- Yeah.

07:04.048 --> 07:07.250
If I want Thai, I go--
I go to a Thai place.

07:07.268 --> 07:09.886
I mean, what is the--
what is the earthly point...

07:09.920 --> 07:10.887
Did I marry you?

07:10.921 --> 07:12.222
...in comparing pizza
to Thai food?

07:12.256 --> 07:13.807
What has happened
to your intelligence?

07:13.858 --> 07:15.608
- This is different.
- They're completely--

07:15.643 --> 07:18.645
Oh, come on,
are you the man I married?

07:18.696 --> 07:21.264
I am the guy who
wants to end this

07:21.282 --> 07:22.765
ridiculous conversation,

07:22.783 --> 07:23.933
kick off my shoes,

07:23.951 --> 07:26.069
and have a very large
glass of wine.

07:26.103 --> 07:28.371
Well, I'm gonna tell you

07:28.405 --> 07:32.275
to be my guest.

07:32.293 --> 07:33.409
All right, wait.

07:33.443 --> 07:36.129
The answer is...
[Keypad beeps]

07:36.163 --> 07:37.664
21.

07:37.715 --> 07:39.249
- No.
- Yes.

07:39.283 --> 07:41.951
Yes, because it has history.

07:41.969 --> 07:43.619
Come on.

07:43.637 --> 07:45.088
Prohibition.

07:45.122 --> 07:46.789
<i>The sweet smell of success.</i>

07:46.807 --> 07:48.474
[Elliott] And per se
has Thomas Keller.

07:48.509 --> 07:50.293
Game, set, and match.

07:50.311 --> 07:52.345
[Gretchen] The whole
vibe is so Yountville.

07:52.396 --> 07:53.629
You transplant it to Manhattan,

07:53.647 --> 07:55.398
- it starts to feel--
- You could transplant it

07:55.432 --> 07:57.317
to Islamabad,
I would still eat there.

07:57.351 --> 07:58.801
Ooh, there's a good thought.

07:58.819 --> 08:01.654
- What, Islamabad?
- No, Napa. We have to go to Napa.

08:01.689 --> 08:03.907
Oh, my God,
all this talk of food.

08:03.941 --> 08:06.409
Do you think Juana
left us anything?

08:06.443 --> 08:07.827
No, I don't think so,

08:07.862 --> 08:09.979
she thought that we were
coming back on Wednesday.

08:09.997 --> 08:11.247
Unless you told her otherwise.

08:11.282 --> 08:12.582
No, I haven't talked to her.

08:12.616 --> 08:14.701
Oh, look, here.

08:14.752 --> 08:17.086
Just a pear,
that'll be perfect.

08:17.121 --> 08:20.039
- Yeah.
- You wanna get us a nice bottle of wine?

08:20.090 --> 08:21.708
Mm-hmm.

08:21.759 --> 08:23.042
Do you think
we have any of those--

08:23.093 --> 08:25.678
what are those
crackers with the,

08:25.713 --> 08:27.881
like, the sun-dried
tomato and then

08:27.932 --> 08:29.382
they were kind of
slightly peppery,

08:29.433 --> 08:30.934
but not too peppery.

08:30.968 --> 08:32.001
We don't have them?

08:34.357 --> 08:35.808
I don't know.
Ask Juana.

08:35.844 --> 08:37.395
We haven't had them in forever.

08:37.431 --> 08:39.344
I don't know why she
doesn't get those anymore.

08:39.379 --> 08:40.429
Why don't you talk to her?

08:40.546 --> 08:42.855
I don't know, she's got that thing
going on with her daughter.

08:42.856 --> 08:43.956
Anyway, Napa?

08:44.030 --> 08:45.181
Yeah?

08:45.199 --> 08:46.649
How long is it since
we've been there?

08:46.683 --> 08:47.700
Two years, Thanksgiving.

08:47.735 --> 08:49.869
- Jesus, that's two years.
- Yeah.

08:49.904 --> 08:52.121
- Too long, right?
- Is this okay?

08:52.156 --> 08:53.823
Oh, that looks perfecto.

08:53.857 --> 08:55.909
You wanna get the fireplace?

08:55.960 --> 08:58.194
[Mutters]

08:58.212 --> 08:59.362
- Is it good?
- Mm-hmm.

08:59.380 --> 09:01.214
- Is it ripe?
- Mm-hmm.

09:01.248 --> 09:03.466
Yeah.

09:03.500 --> 09:05.752
[Gretchen] You know, we could
invite George and Delores,

09:05.803 --> 09:07.220
they could come up from Marin.

09:07.254 --> 09:09.555
And Bill and Miriam Cohen.

09:09.590 --> 09:13.376
We could have a little
spa action, right?

09:13.394 --> 09:15.878
And then we could do some
sort of wine, and then--

09:15.896 --> 09:17.397
Aah!

09:25.239 --> 09:27.523
Hello, Gretchen.

09:27.557 --> 09:29.525
Elliott.

09:31.245 --> 09:33.896
I really like your new house.

09:35.950 --> 09:37.667
Walt.

09:39.569 --> 09:41.570
This...

09:48.012 --> 09:50.930
Are we looking east?

09:50.965 --> 09:52.215
Oh.

09:52.249 --> 09:55.268
My God, you must
have one great view

09:55.302 --> 09:57.353
of the Sangre De Cristos.

09:57.388 --> 09:58.421
Walt,

09:58.439 --> 10:00.440
what-- what are
you doing here?

10:02.426 --> 10:05.928
I saw you on <i>Charlie Rose.</i>

10:05.946 --> 10:09.282
You looked great.

10:09.316 --> 10:10.450
You both did.

10:10.484 --> 10:13.403
If you are here to--

10:13.437 --> 10:14.954
to hurt us--

10:14.989 --> 10:16.990
Walt, whatever

10:17.041 --> 10:18.958
it is you're planning--

10:18.993 --> 10:21.044
Actually, I'm here
to give you something.

10:23.780 --> 10:26.249
It's out in my car.

10:26.283 --> 10:28.617
How about the three of us
take a walk to it?

10:28.635 --> 10:30.619
It's just parked down the road.

10:30.637 --> 10:33.222
I couldn't get it
past your gate.

10:40.297 --> 10:42.965
Elliott,

10:42.983 --> 10:44.984
if we're gonna go that way,

10:45.019 --> 10:47.653
you'll need a bigger knife.

10:52.910 --> 10:54.694
[Knife clatters]

10:57.544 --> 10:58.744
[Walt] Keep stacking.

10:58.778 --> 11:02.097
It'll all fit.

11:02.148 --> 11:04.399
[Coughs]

11:06.569 --> 11:09.387
That's all right.

11:09.405 --> 11:11.990
Just-- just
throw it on top.

11:14.994 --> 11:16.394
Gretchen, would you mind?

11:16.412 --> 11:19.081
We don't want to lose
any under the furniture.

11:22.418 --> 11:24.753
All right.

11:24.787 --> 11:29.207
That is $9,720,000.

11:29.241 --> 11:30.626
Where did it come from?

11:30.677 --> 11:33.679
And why is it here?

11:33.713 --> 11:35.047
I earned it,

11:35.081 --> 11:36.748
and you're going to
give it to my children.

11:36.766 --> 11:38.216
What? Why?

11:38.250 --> 11:39.405
Walt, I don't
think we--

11:39.515 --> 11:41.353
On my son's 18th birthday,

11:41.387 --> 11:42.638
which is ten months

11:42.689 --> 11:44.923
and two days from today,

11:44.941 --> 11:47.092
you will give him this money

11:47.110 --> 11:49.278
in the form
of an irrevocable trust.

11:49.312 --> 11:51.446
You will tell him
that it is his

11:51.481 --> 11:54.432
to do with as he sees fit,

11:54.450 --> 11:56.151
but with the hope

11:56.202 --> 11:59.538
that he uses it for
his college education.

11:59.572 --> 12:01.373
And for the betterment
of his family.

12:01.407 --> 12:04.609
Walt, I'm not sure
that we follow.

12:04.627 --> 12:07.462
Why, uh, I mean,

12:07.497 --> 12:09.331
why, in particular,
would we--

12:09.382 --> 12:11.133
If you wanna give
your kids drug money,

12:11.167 --> 12:12.501
go do it yourself.

12:12.552 --> 12:14.219
I can't.

12:14.253 --> 12:16.672
My wife and son hate me.

12:16.723 --> 12:19.391
They won't take my money.

12:19.425 --> 12:21.093
Even if they did,

12:21.127 --> 12:23.478
the federal government
wouldn't let them.

12:25.565 --> 12:27.649
But two rich benefactors,

12:27.684 --> 12:30.319
who are known for their
charitable endeavors,

12:30.353 --> 12:32.137
who would think nothing
of, for instance,

12:32.155 --> 12:34.439
writing a $28 million check

12:34.473 --> 12:38.360
to help victims of
methamphetamine abuse?

12:38.411 --> 12:40.779
I have to think that your money

12:40.813 --> 12:41.997
would be very welcome.

12:42.031 --> 12:44.315
It wouldn't make
any sense coming from us.

12:44.334 --> 12:45.984
It certainly would.

12:46.002 --> 12:48.153
My children are
blameless victims

12:48.171 --> 12:50.839
of their monstrous father.

12:50.873 --> 12:53.375
A man who you
once knew quite well.

12:59.766 --> 13:00.832
Call it a beau geste,

13:00.850 --> 13:02.184
call it liberal guilt,

13:02.218 --> 13:03.552
call it whatever you want,

13:03.603 --> 13:05.504
but do it.

13:05.538 --> 13:08.640
And you are not to spend

13:08.675 --> 13:12.277
a single dime
of your own money.

13:12.311 --> 13:13.879
If there are taxes

13:13.913 --> 13:16.548
or lawyers' fees owed,

13:16.582 --> 13:18.316
you will take it
right from here.

13:18.351 --> 13:21.236
They use my money, never yours.

13:21.287 --> 13:22.854
Okay, Walt, sure.

13:22.872 --> 13:25.123
That--
that sounds reasonable.

13:27.377 --> 13:30.245
So what happens next?

13:30.296 --> 13:32.581
I guess we shake on it,

13:32.632 --> 13:34.633
and I leave.

14:03.946 --> 14:06.748
I can trust you to do this.

14:06.783 --> 14:08.250
Yes.

14:08.284 --> 14:11.286
Absolutely you can.

14:25.918 --> 14:26.968
Oh!

14:27.019 --> 14:28.637
Don't move.
Don't...

14:28.688 --> 14:30.105
Don't dare move a muscle.

14:30.139 --> 14:31.273
You don't want them to think

14:31.307 --> 14:33.058
that you're trying to get away.

14:33.092 --> 14:34.476
Just breathe.

14:37.063 --> 14:38.263
Just this afternoon,

14:38.281 --> 14:40.398
I had an extra $200,000

14:40.432 --> 14:41.783
that I would have loved dearly

14:41.818 --> 14:45.153
to leave on top of this table.

14:45.204 --> 14:46.955
Instead,

14:46.989 --> 14:48.824
I gave it to the two best

14:48.875 --> 14:52.244
hitmen west of the Mississippi.

14:52.278 --> 14:54.612
Now,

14:54.630 --> 14:59.835
whatever happens
to me tomorrow,

14:59.886 --> 15:01.970
they'll still be out there.

15:03.973 --> 15:06.791
Keeping tabs.

15:06.809 --> 15:08.176
And if,

15:08.227 --> 15:10.345
for any reason,

15:10.396 --> 15:14.465
that my children
do not get this money,

15:14.484 --> 15:16.685
a kind of...

15:16.736 --> 15:18.970
countdown will begin.

15:19.005 --> 15:21.306
Maybe a day or so later,

15:21.324 --> 15:22.774
maybe a week, a year,

15:22.808 --> 15:24.826
when you're going for
a walk in Santa Fe

15:24.861 --> 15:27.812
or Manhattan
or Prague, wherever,

15:27.830 --> 15:29.831
and you're...

15:29.866 --> 15:32.868
talking about
your stock prices...

15:35.171 --> 15:39.424
without a worry in the world.

15:39.458 --> 15:42.043
And then suddenly,

15:42.094 --> 15:43.929
you'll hear the scrape

15:43.963 --> 15:45.380
of a footstep behind you,

15:45.431 --> 15:47.465
but before you can
even turn around,

15:47.499 --> 15:49.500
- pop!
- Aah!

15:54.357 --> 15:56.358
Darkness.

16:02.398 --> 16:05.033
Cheer up, beautiful people.

16:07.320 --> 16:10.071
This is where
you get to make it right.

16:23.336 --> 16:26.338
[Gretchen sobs]

16:58.237 --> 17:00.238
Oh, yeah, right.

17:08.347 --> 17:09.513
You know, I don't exactly

17:09.548 --> 17:11.683
know how to feel
about all this.

17:11.717 --> 17:13.184
For real, yo.

17:13.219 --> 17:15.854
Whole thing felt kinda shady,
you know, like,

17:15.887 --> 17:17.055
morality-wise?

17:17.089 --> 17:19.089
Totally.

17:20.592 --> 17:24.429
How do you feel now?

17:24.446 --> 17:25.596
Better.

17:25.615 --> 17:28.433
Yeah, definitely improving.

17:28.451 --> 17:29.985
[Walt] What's this I hear about

17:30.036 --> 17:33.622
blue meth still
being out there?

17:33.656 --> 17:34.623
What do you mean?

17:34.657 --> 17:36.458
Have you heard anything?

17:36.492 --> 17:38.493
Is it still being sold?

17:40.997 --> 17:42.998
Yeah.

17:47.336 --> 17:49.387
By whom?

17:49.422 --> 17:52.557
It's you, right?

17:52.591 --> 17:54.509
I mean, aren't you
still cooking?

17:57.980 --> 17:59.230
Damn, man.

17:59.265 --> 18:00.932
We were sure it was you,

18:00.966 --> 18:02.600
because that shit
is choice, yo.

18:02.634 --> 18:03.985
Better than ever.

18:04.020 --> 18:06.354
I mean, um, you know.

18:08.658 --> 18:09.858
Jesse.

18:09.909 --> 18:10.975
Seriously?

18:10.993 --> 18:12.694
You said he moved to Alaska.

18:12.745 --> 18:14.812
That's what I heard.

18:14.830 --> 18:15.947
Right on, Jesse.

18:15.981 --> 18:17.982
Passing the torch.

18:17.983 --> 18:21.230
Damn, man, couldn't he at least
throw a brother a bone?

19:08.351 --> 19:10.452
[Blows]

20:02.839 --> 20:06.508
Wow, what happened there?

20:06.542 --> 20:08.126
It's my birthday.

20:08.177 --> 20:10.595
Yeah? Well,
happy birthday.

20:58.478 --> 21:00.128
[Hank] <i>It's easy money.</i>

21:00.146 --> 21:01.646
<i>Until we catch you.</i>

21:01.681 --> 21:02.764
Walt, just say the word

21:02.798 --> 21:04.466
and I'll take you
on a ride-along.

21:04.484 --> 21:06.651
You can watch us knock down
a meth lab, huh?

21:06.686 --> 21:09.571
Get a little excitement
in your life.

21:09.605 --> 21:11.940
Someday.

21:38.935 --> 21:40.001
Welcome to The Grove.

21:40.019 --> 21:41.103
Would you like to see a menu?

21:41.137 --> 21:42.187
No, thank you.

21:42.221 --> 21:44.022
Chamomile tea
with soy milk, please.

21:44.056 --> 21:45.840
All right, you got it.

22:01.290 --> 22:03.458
Hey, how you doing?

22:03.493 --> 22:05.377
Good.

22:05.411 --> 22:07.662
How's things?

22:07.696 --> 22:09.697
Hey, I like your...

22:12.084 --> 22:13.368
shirt.

22:13.386 --> 22:14.386
My blouse?

22:14.420 --> 22:16.371
Nice, yeah, the color.

22:16.389 --> 22:19.558
That's a nice color on you.

22:19.592 --> 22:20.926
It's kind of a--

22:20.977 --> 22:22.511
I don't know exactly
what you'd call it.

22:22.545 --> 22:26.231
It's kind of a cornflower.

22:26.265 --> 22:27.566
Before you say or do anything,

22:27.600 --> 22:30.435
just hear me out.

22:30.486 --> 22:31.553
Todd--

22:31.571 --> 22:32.887
Nobody knows that I'm here.

22:32.905 --> 22:34.856
Just listen for two minutes

22:34.890 --> 22:36.408
and then I'll leave.

22:36.442 --> 22:37.776
Please.

22:37.827 --> 22:39.161
Please.

22:39.195 --> 22:40.562
Just two minutes of your time.

22:40.580 --> 22:43.582
That's all I ask.

22:44.750 --> 22:45.867
Please.

22:52.008 --> 22:54.676
You're running out
of methylamine, aren't you?

22:54.710 --> 22:57.212
I can do the math.

22:57.246 --> 22:58.547
You've been at it long enough.

22:58.581 --> 23:01.516
You must be running low.

23:01.551 --> 23:04.719
I have a new method

23:04.753 --> 23:06.638
that requires no methylamine.

23:06.689 --> 23:07.889
And it's easy, and it will

23:07.923 --> 23:09.090
keep you in business.

23:09.108 --> 23:11.593
And Todd, I could
teach it to you.

23:11.611 --> 23:14.779
How did you know
to find us here?

23:14.814 --> 23:17.782
10:00 AM
every Tuesday morning,

23:17.817 --> 23:19.734
you and I met here.

23:19.768 --> 23:21.603
You're rather...

23:21.621 --> 23:23.371
schedule-oriented,
I guess.

23:23.406 --> 23:26.608
[Coughs]

23:37.503 --> 23:39.954
Sorry.

23:45.961 --> 23:48.763
I need the money.

23:48.797 --> 23:51.683
I've spent almost all of mine.

23:51.734 --> 23:54.236
Already, just trying to stay

23:54.270 --> 23:56.655
one step ahead of the police.

23:56.689 --> 23:59.658
Mr. White, I don't
think there's--

23:59.692 --> 24:04.329
How much would it cost us?

24:04.363 --> 24:06.114
Nothing short of a million,

24:06.148 --> 24:07.666
and believe me, for this,

24:07.700 --> 24:11.536
that is--
is giving it away.

24:11.587 --> 24:12.987
I think Jack should hear this.

24:13.005 --> 24:14.873
Yeah, I don't know.

24:14.924 --> 24:17.325
Now listen, I can--

24:17.343 --> 24:19.294
I can come up there tonight

24:19.328 --> 24:21.296
and talk to him.

24:21.330 --> 24:23.164
He'd get it.

24:23.182 --> 24:26.718
This is a win-win
situation.

24:26.769 --> 24:28.470
Hi, what can I get for you two?

24:28.504 --> 24:29.971
He's just leaving.

24:30.005 --> 24:32.524
Good seeing you again.
Take care.

24:36.178 --> 24:38.012
For you?

24:38.030 --> 24:39.230
I'm good.

24:39.282 --> 24:41.700
And I need more stevia.

24:51.294 --> 24:52.744
Okay, no disrespect to the man,

24:52.795 --> 24:54.379
but doing business with him?

24:54.413 --> 24:55.747
Right now,
that's not--

24:55.798 --> 24:58.583
Of course, we're not
doing business with him.

25:00.136 --> 25:01.869
Todd, please.

25:01.887 --> 25:04.038
Don't make me
walk you through this.

25:07.977 --> 25:10.979
Jesus.
Did you look at him?

25:12.765 --> 25:15.767
You'd be doing him a favor.

25:36.766 --> 25:38.767
[Walt coughs]

25:45.959 --> 25:47.593
[Walt hums]

25:47.627 --> 25:50.045
[Humming continues]

25:56.803 --> 25:59.271
[Coughs]

25:59.305 --> 26:01.306
[Humming resumes]

26:12.202 --> 26:13.702
[Alarm chirps]

26:47.203 --> 26:49.137
[Alarm chirps]

26:50.173 --> 26:54.109
[Phone ringing]

27:01.984 --> 27:04.253
<i>[Electronic voice] Hello,
please record after the tone.</i>

27:04.287 --> 27:05.504
<i>[Beep]</i>

27:05.538 --> 27:07.656
<i>[Marie] Truce, all right?</i>

27:07.674 --> 27:09.324
<i>Skyler, I have news about Walt,</i>

27:09.342 --> 27:10.825
<i>and you need</i>
<i>to hear it immediately,</i>

27:10.843 --> 27:14.129
<i>so if you're there, pick up.</i>

27:14.163 --> 27:16.665
<i>Skyler--</i>
[Phone beeps]

27:16.683 --> 27:19.468
Hey.

27:19.502 --> 27:21.270
What's up?

27:21.304 --> 27:23.522
<i>Walt's in town.</i>

27:23.556 --> 27:24.690
Yeah?

27:24.724 --> 27:26.475
That car they thought he stole

27:26.509 --> 27:27.643
in New Hampshire,

27:27.677 --> 27:29.227
they found it in
a Denny's parking lot

27:29.279 --> 27:30.845
right on Central.

27:30.863 --> 27:32.698
<i>And your old</i>
<i>next-door neighbor,</i>

27:32.732 --> 27:34.483
<i>the one on the right,</i>
<i>what's her name, Becky?</i>

27:34.517 --> 27:36.702
Becky's on the left.
Carol's on the right.

27:36.736 --> 27:38.320
<i>Becky, Carol, whatever.</i>

27:38.354 --> 27:40.855
<i>She saw him at your old house.</i>

27:40.873 --> 27:43.125
Just this morning,
plain as day.

27:43.159 --> 27:45.193
He's there, walking
out of your house,

27:45.211 --> 27:47.879
and he calls her by name.

27:47.914 --> 27:50.382
He didn't hurt her, did he?
He didn't--

27:50.416 --> 27:52.701
No, he's just like,
"Hey, Becky!"

27:52.719 --> 27:55.387
Or Carol, whatever.

27:55.421 --> 27:58.173
<i>She said he looked</i>
<i>exactly like the Unabomber,</i>

27:58.207 --> 27:59.841
<i>but she's positive it was him.</i>

27:59.875 --> 28:01.927
Skyler, we're getting
calls from all over town.

28:01.978 --> 28:03.512
He's here, he's there,

28:03.546 --> 28:05.063
he's going
to blow up city hall.

28:05.098 --> 28:06.732
Apparently he has
some sort of manifesto.

28:06.766 --> 28:08.233
He wants to be on
the six o'clock news.

28:08.267 --> 28:10.602
<i>- It's just--</i>
- Who's making these calls, him?

28:10.653 --> 28:12.154
<i>There are two or three</i>
<i>different voices.</i>

28:12.188 --> 28:13.722
<i>They're not sure</i>
<i>if they're crank calls</i>

28:13.740 --> 28:15.574
<i>or people he's put up to it</i>

28:15.608 --> 28:18.026
<i>or if they're actual</i>
<i>anonymous tips.</i>

28:18.060 --> 28:19.194
<i>And it's stretching them thin,</i>

28:19.228 --> 28:20.729
<i>which is maybe the point.</i>

28:20.747 --> 28:22.531
<i>As far as I'm concerned,</i>
<i>and I've told them this,</i>

28:22.565 --> 28:24.199
there are three places
that he would go.

28:24.233 --> 28:26.568
To you, to me, or Flynn.

28:26.586 --> 28:28.570
<i>Right.</i>

28:28.588 --> 28:30.238
They're watching
the high school.

28:30.256 --> 28:33.759
They're probably
watching your place, too.

28:33.793 --> 28:36.094
I mean,

28:36.129 --> 28:38.797
I know that's what
Hank would do.

28:38.848 --> 28:40.799
There's no way
Walt's getting to you.

28:40.850 --> 28:43.635
They are absolutely
going to catch him.

28:43.686 --> 28:44.936
No doubt about it.

28:44.971 --> 28:46.388
That arrogant asshole thinks

28:46.422 --> 28:47.922
he's some criminal mastermind,

28:47.940 --> 28:49.474
but he's not.

28:49.525 --> 28:51.426
<i>But on the off-chance...</i>

28:51.444 --> 28:53.445
Yeah.

28:53.479 --> 28:56.898
On the million-to-one
chance...

28:58.651 --> 29:00.318
you be on the lookout, okay?

29:04.657 --> 29:06.408
Thanks.

29:09.212 --> 29:11.613
You got it.

29:13.833 --> 29:16.334
[Phone beeps]

29:29.199 --> 29:31.700
Five minutes.

29:38.291 --> 29:40.792
Five minutes.

29:46.082 --> 29:47.799
You didn't kill anybody

29:47.834 --> 29:51.386
sneaking in here, did you?

29:51.421 --> 29:52.671
You didn't hurt anybody?

29:52.722 --> 29:54.806
No.

29:54.841 --> 29:57.342
Didn't have to.

30:08.738 --> 30:11.607
You look terrible.

30:11.641 --> 30:14.743
Yeah.

30:14.777 --> 30:17.863
But I feel good.

30:17.914 --> 30:20.916
So talk.

30:22.368 --> 30:24.002
Why are you here?

30:34.547 --> 30:37.766
It's over.

30:37.800 --> 30:42.104
And I needed a proper goodbye.

30:42.138 --> 30:44.139
Not our last phone call.

30:46.025 --> 30:48.527
So you're going to the police?

30:50.897 --> 30:52.814
They'll be coming to me.

30:52.848 --> 30:57.319
If you're in custody,

30:57.353 --> 30:59.037
what stops those people
from coming back,

30:59.072 --> 31:00.855
those people you worked with?

31:00.873 --> 31:05.877
When-- when I still
had the house,

31:05.912 --> 31:07.045
three men came

31:07.080 --> 31:08.380
in the middle of the night,

31:08.414 --> 31:11.466
wearing masks, threatening
Holly and Flynn and me.

31:11.501 --> 31:13.385
They told me not to talk about

31:13.419 --> 31:14.720
that woman I saw
at the car wash,

31:14.754 --> 31:16.588
and if you're in custody
and they find out--

31:16.639 --> 31:17.872
They're not coming back.

31:17.890 --> 31:20.559
Not after tonight.

31:20.593 --> 31:22.561
What's tonight?

31:28.735 --> 31:32.854
We don't want your money, Walt.

31:32.888 --> 31:35.240
I thought Flynn
made that clear.

31:35.274 --> 31:37.492
He did.

31:37.527 --> 31:40.729
And I don't have any
to give you.

31:40.747 --> 31:45.334
I spent the last
of it getting here.

31:45.368 --> 31:48.737
All I have to give you

31:48.755 --> 31:50.756
is this.

32:01.751 --> 32:04.052
Call the DEA once I leave.

32:04.086 --> 32:05.771
Tell them I was here.

32:05.805 --> 32:08.523
That I forced my way in.

32:08.558 --> 32:12.927
Tell them...

32:12.945 --> 32:14.780
Tell them I wanted
bacon and eggs

32:14.814 --> 32:17.983
on my birthday,

32:18.034 --> 32:21.536
and that I gave you
that ticket.

32:21.571 --> 32:25.624
Those numbers
are GPS coordinates.

32:25.658 --> 32:27.659
For what?

32:30.329 --> 32:33.582
A burial site.

32:33.616 --> 32:36.618
That's where they'll
find Hank and Steve Gomez.

32:40.306 --> 32:43.792
That's where
I buried our money.

32:43.810 --> 32:46.561
The men who stole it from us,

32:46.596 --> 32:49.514
the men who still have it,

32:49.565 --> 32:51.983
they murdered Hank and Steve

32:52.018 --> 32:54.519
and put them in that hole.

32:56.439 --> 32:58.740
Now you trade that

32:58.775 --> 33:01.309
for a deal with the prosecutor.

33:01.327 --> 33:04.196
You get yourself out of this.

33:04.247 --> 33:06.248
Skyler.

33:08.584 --> 33:10.585
Skyler.

33:13.673 --> 33:17.175
All the things that I did,

33:17.210 --> 33:18.326
you need
to understand--

33:18.344 --> 33:21.096
If I have to hear

33:21.130 --> 33:23.765
one more time

33:23.800 --> 33:25.600
that you did this

33:25.635 --> 33:26.768
for the family--

33:26.803 --> 33:28.804
I did it for me.

33:35.511 --> 33:40.348
I liked it.

33:40.366 --> 33:42.701
I was good at it.

33:44.821 --> 33:47.239
And...

33:47.290 --> 33:49.791
I was...

33:49.826 --> 33:52.527
really...

33:56.632 --> 33:58.633
I was alive.

34:37.790 --> 34:40.458
Flynn will be home soon.

34:42.094 --> 34:44.094
Before I go...

34:46.599 --> 34:48.600
may I see her?

37:28.646 --> 37:30.880
Whoo.

37:32.650 --> 37:34.984
Damn man,
this thing's a classic.

37:35.019 --> 37:36.385
What block you got in it?

37:36.404 --> 37:39.406
500 or the 425?

37:41.158 --> 37:44.160
Couldn't tell you.

37:50.251 --> 37:52.869
500.

37:52.903 --> 37:55.338
That's the one you want.

37:55.372 --> 37:58.591
No replacement
for displacement.

38:08.886 --> 38:10.419
Where to?

38:10.438 --> 38:12.455
To the clubhouse.

38:28.239 --> 38:29.572
Just go ahead, just park it

38:29.606 --> 38:31.607
right in front over here.

38:33.610 --> 38:35.161
No, no, no,
just straight in, man,

38:35.212 --> 38:38.214
just, what are...

38:38.249 --> 38:41.251
All right, fine,
here, whatever.

38:44.805 --> 38:46.806
[Walt coughs]

38:51.679 --> 38:55.098
Hey, how you doing?

38:55.132 --> 38:58.134
Turn around, put your
arms out like this.

39:18.873 --> 39:20.173
While you're at it,

39:20.207 --> 39:21.841
why don't you
lift your shirt up?

39:21.876 --> 39:24.511
Give us a spin.

39:24.545 --> 39:26.829
Christ, I'm not wearing a wire.

39:41.862 --> 39:43.863
Okay?

39:45.149 --> 39:46.349
My wallet and keys?

39:46.367 --> 39:47.483
Yeah, you'll get them back.

39:47.517 --> 39:49.018
Just relax.

39:51.355 --> 39:53.356
[Whistles]

40:01.081 --> 40:02.632
Stay here.

40:02.666 --> 40:06.252
Keep your eyes open.

40:06.303 --> 40:08.537
[Jack] Jesus, look at you
with that head of hair.

40:08.556 --> 40:10.139
Is that real?

40:10.174 --> 40:11.808
Yes.

40:11.842 --> 40:12.976
That's not a wig?

40:13.010 --> 40:14.177
Seriously?

40:14.211 --> 40:15.511
No.

40:15.545 --> 40:18.481
What were you doing before,
shaving it?

40:18.515 --> 40:19.566
Yes.

40:19.600 --> 40:23.353
Christ, that is one
fine head of hair.

40:23.387 --> 40:25.188
I mean, otherwise you
look like shit, but--

40:25.222 --> 40:27.740
Hello to you too, Jack.

40:27.775 --> 40:29.993
Can we talk business?

40:30.027 --> 40:32.862
I don't think so, no.

40:32.896 --> 40:34.831
Did Todd tell you
what I'm offering?

40:34.865 --> 40:36.399
Yeah, he told me.

40:36.417 --> 40:38.201
Thing is, we're...

40:38.235 --> 40:39.953
not really in the market.

40:42.206 --> 40:43.623
You're running low
on methylamine,

40:43.674 --> 40:44.757
what happens then?

40:44.792 --> 40:47.877
No, we'll get more.

40:47.911 --> 40:49.429
That Quayle woman's
got her own set-up.

40:49.463 --> 40:51.247
The heat's off her.

40:51.265 --> 40:53.082
She can break loose a barrel
every now and again.

40:53.100 --> 40:54.851
It ain't broke, so why fix it?

40:54.885 --> 40:57.637
Todd, please, would you
explain things to your uncle?

40:57.688 --> 41:00.306
Explain to him the benefit
of what I'm offering.

41:01.775 --> 41:05.061
You really shouldn't
have come back, Mr. White.

41:06.814 --> 41:08.815
I'm sorry.

41:11.452 --> 41:12.785
Wait. Jack.

41:12.820 --> 41:13.936
Where do you want it?

41:13.954 --> 41:15.438
Well, gee, I don't know,

41:15.456 --> 41:16.539
anywhere but my living room?

41:16.573 --> 41:17.606
Take him out back.

41:17.625 --> 41:19.208
- Jack, you owe me.
- Hey, come on.

41:19.243 --> 41:20.827
- You owe me.
- Hey, hey, hey.

41:20.878 --> 41:22.611
I owe you, what for?

41:22.630 --> 41:24.163
Jesse Pinkman,
you promised that

41:24.214 --> 41:26.132
you would kill him,
and you didn't.

41:26.166 --> 41:28.418
Instead, you
partnered with him.

41:28.452 --> 41:29.618
You're his
partner now--

41:29.637 --> 41:31.804
Whoa, whoa, whoa, stop.

41:38.729 --> 41:40.930
Partners,
what are you talking about?

41:40.964 --> 41:42.631
He's alive, isn't he?

41:42.650 --> 41:44.967
He's cooking for you.

41:44.985 --> 41:47.737
What, are you gonna lie?

41:47.771 --> 41:48.938
Him being alive is not

41:48.972 --> 41:50.657
him and me being partners.

41:50.691 --> 41:52.659
Not by a damn sight.

41:52.693 --> 41:54.944
What, you think
I'd partner with a rat?

41:54.978 --> 41:56.946
Where's that little
piece of shit?

41:56.980 --> 41:58.614
He's finishing up a batch.

41:58.648 --> 42:00.333
Well, go get him.
Bring him here.

42:02.369 --> 42:04.120
- Uncle Jack--
- No. No, no, no.

42:04.154 --> 42:06.122
This one here
calling me a liar?

42:06.156 --> 42:09.175
He just insulted you,
he insulted me, all of us.

42:09.209 --> 42:11.511
Jesus. Hustle it up.
Come on.

42:11.545 --> 42:14.464
Let's get this over with.

42:14.498 --> 42:18.384
I'm gonna show you
just how wrong you are,

42:18.435 --> 42:22.138
then I'm putting that bullet
in your head myself.

42:44.044 --> 42:46.829
[Air whooshing]

42:51.218 --> 42:53.553
[Whooshing continues]

43:16.660 --> 43:19.996
You see what I'm talking about,
you son of a bitch?

43:20.030 --> 43:22.064
[Grumbles]

43:22.082 --> 43:23.583
[Grunts]

43:24.901 --> 43:26.869
Now, this look like
a partner to you?

43:26.903 --> 43:29.839
Come here.
Take a look.

43:29.873 --> 43:31.874
Come here!

43:42.436 --> 43:44.437
Take a look at him.

43:44.471 --> 43:46.973
Have a gander.

43:47.024 --> 43:49.025
This is my partner.

43:49.059 --> 43:52.445
Right, partner?
Right, buddy?

43:53.730 --> 43:56.599
Hardworking, good partner.
50-50 partner.

44:00.654 --> 44:02.955
Can you hurry this shit up?
Make it quick?

44:08.462 --> 44:10.046
[Yells]

44:10.080 --> 44:11.964
[Both grunting]

44:11.999 --> 44:13.499
Toddy, get him off, would ya?

44:13.550 --> 44:15.284
Yeah, Toddy, get them both off.

44:15.302 --> 44:17.887
[Laughter]
[Alarm chirps]

44:20.591 --> 44:21.724
Aah!

44:22.843 --> 44:24.260
[Men grunting]

44:51.371 --> 44:52.988
[Grunts]

45:13.810 --> 45:17.196
[Whooshing continues]

45:24.821 --> 45:26.289
[Grunts]

45:26.323 --> 45:29.024
[Coughing]

45:31.861 --> 45:33.362
Uncle Jack...

45:35.198 --> 45:37.583
[Groaning]

45:49.146 --> 45:51.397
[Grunts]

45:51.431 --> 45:52.732
Jesus.

45:52.766 --> 45:55.050
[Chain rattling]

45:55.068 --> 45:56.569
Mr. White...

45:56.603 --> 45:58.187
[Grunts]
Aah!

45:58.221 --> 45:59.888
[Grunting loudly]

46:03.110 --> 46:05.494
[Grunting continues]

46:22.245 --> 46:23.713
[Clattering]

46:23.747 --> 46:26.599
[Grunting continues]
[Muffled gasps]

46:38.261 --> 46:39.779
[Crunch]

46:45.101 --> 46:47.936
[Breathing heavily]

46:58.615 --> 47:01.217
[Muffled coughing]

47:05.088 --> 47:07.790
[Coughing continues]
Wait.

47:07.808 --> 47:09.308
Wait.

47:17.851 --> 47:19.852
You want your money, right?

47:19.903 --> 47:21.970
Huh?

47:21.989 --> 47:23.990
You wanna know where it is?

47:25.692 --> 47:27.994
You pull that trigger,
you'll never...

47:28.028 --> 47:29.695
[Body thuds]

47:40.824 --> 47:43.676
[Panting]

48:17.377 --> 48:19.328
Do it.

48:28.037 --> 48:30.038
You want this.

48:31.224 --> 48:33.309
Say the words.

48:35.062 --> 48:37.596
Say you want this!

48:39.182 --> 48:42.651
Nothing happens
until I hear you say it.

48:45.054 --> 48:47.055
[Quietly]
I want this.

49:09.763 --> 49:11.764
Then do it yourself.

49:42.129 --> 49:45.131
<i>[Line ringing]</i>
Pick up the phone.

49:48.618 --> 49:50.386
<i>Hello?</i>

49:50.420 --> 49:52.304
Is it done?

49:52.339 --> 49:54.340
Is he gone?

49:54.391 --> 49:56.842
<i>Yeah, it's done.</i>

49:56.893 --> 49:58.811
<i>He's gone.</i>

49:58.845 --> 50:00.763
<i>They're all gone.</i>

50:00.797 --> 50:03.766
Todd?
Who is this?

50:04.768 --> 50:07.069
It's Walt.

50:07.103 --> 50:09.071
How are you feeling?

50:09.105 --> 50:12.307
Kind of under the weather?

50:12.325 --> 50:15.161
Like you've got the flu?

50:15.195 --> 50:17.163
That would be the ricin
I gave you.

50:17.197 --> 50:20.249
<i>I slipped it into</i>
<i>that stevia crap</i>

50:20.283 --> 50:23.285
<i>that you're always putting</i>
<i>in your tea.</i>

50:23.319 --> 50:25.320
[Whispers] Oh, my God.

50:28.291 --> 50:30.209
Well...

50:32.295 --> 50:34.346
goodbye, Lydia.

51:07.864 --> 51:09.665
[Engine starts]

51:17.007 --> 51:18.340
[Tires squeal]

51:25.849 --> 51:27.816
[Hysterical laughter]

51:27.851 --> 51:29.852
[Thudding]

51:34.574 --> 51:35.724
Aahh!

51:35.742 --> 51:38.193
[Garage door motor
whirring softly]

51:47.287 --> 51:50.456
[Grunts]

51:57.714 --> 51:58.881
[Coughs]

52:28.328 --> 52:30.829
[Sirens wailing, distant]

52:47.796 --> 52:50.952
<i>[Male singer]</i>
<i>♪ guess I got what I deserved ♪</i>

52:55.315 --> 52:59.723
<i>♪ kept you waiting there</i>
<i>too long my love ♪</i>

53:02.799 --> 53:06.383
<i>♪ all that time</i>
<i>without a word ♪</i>

53:10.509 --> 53:15.034
<i>♪ didn't know you'd think</i>
<i>that I'd forget ♪</i>

53:17.163 --> 53:18.985
<i>♪ or I'd regret ♪</i>

53:21.803 --> 53:25.630
<i>♪ the special love</i>
<i>I had for you ♪</i>

53:27.848 --> 53:29.344
<i>♪ my baby blue ♪</i>

53:37.408 --> 53:40.928
<i>♪ all the days became so long ♪</i>

53:44.915 --> 53:49.530
<i>♪ did you really think</i>
<i>I'd do you wrong ♪</i>

53:52.563 --> 53:56.429
<i>♪ Dixie, when I let you go ♪</i>

54:00.223 --> 54:04.774
<i>♪ thought you'd realize</i>
<i>that I would know ♪</i>

54:07.277 --> 54:08.749
<i>♪ I would show ♪</i>

54:11.655 --> 54:15.456
<i>♪ the special love</i>
<i>I have for you ♪</i>

54:17.685 --> 54:19.129
<i>♪ my baby blue ♪</i>

